There is no mistaking U2's love for Johannesburg. 
It was one of the first cities in the South Africa to embrace U2, and the early shows in Johannesburg have an energy which is unmistakable. 
This recording is a soundboard recording, and the sound is amazing for such an early show. 
This set captures the entire show, something which other bootlegs of this show fail to do. 
It is cool to hear an early U2 on tour, and there is some great sounding early material in this set
